icks, R.E., Archaeal nucleic acids in picoplankton from great lakes on three continents (2003) Microbial. Ecol., 46, pp. 238-248; Kulongoski, J.T., Hilton, D.R., Selaolo, E.T., Climate variability in the Botswana Kalahari from the late Pleistocene to the present day (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett., 31, pp. L10204. , doi:10.1029/2003GL019238; Lea, D.W., Pak, D.K., Peterson, L.C., Hughen, K.A., Synchroneity of tropical and high-latitude Atlantic temperatures over the last glacial termination (2003) Science, 301, pp. 1361-1364; Liu, Z., Otto-Bleisner, B.L., Kutzbach, J., Li, L., Shields, C., Coupled climate simulation of the evolution of global monsoons in the Holocene (2003) J. Clim., 16, pp. 2472-2490; Patterson, G., Kachinjika, O., Limnology and phytoplankton ecology (1995) The Fishery Potential and Productivity of the Pelagic Zone of Lake Malawi/Niassa, pp. 1-68. , edited by A. Menz, Nat. Resour. Inst., Overseas Dev. Admin., Chatham, UK; Powers, L.A., Werne, J.P., Johnson, T.C., Hopmans, E.C., Damsté, J.S.S., Schouten, S., Crenarchaeotal membrane lipids in lake sediments: A new paleotemperature proxy for continental paleoclimate reconstruction? (2004) Geology, 32, pp. 613-616; Ricketts, R.D., Johnson, T.C., Early Holocene changes in Lake Malawi as interpreted from oxygen and carbon isotopic measurements of authigenic carbonates (1996) The Limnology, Climatology, and Paleoclimatology of the East African Lakes, pp. 475-493. , edited by T. C. Johnson arid E. Odada, Gordon and Breach, New York; Rosell-Melé, A., Bard, E., Emeis, K., Grieger, B., Hewitt, C., Müller, P.J., Schneider, R.R., Sea surface temperature anomalies in the oceans at the LGM estimated from the alkenone-U37 K′ index: Comparison with GCMs (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett., 31, pp. L03208. , doi:10.1029/2003GL018151; Schoutèn, S., Hopmans, E.C., Schefuss, E., Sinninghe Damsté, J.S., Distributional variations in marine crenarchaeotal membrane lipids: A new tool for reconstructing ancient sea water temperatures? (20